%Selket, a tiny Static Site Generator
@Subhaditya Mukherjee

# Steps to make a site
- pip install -r requirements.txt
- Initialize with 
        python selket/runner.py -n "mysimplesite"
- Edit config.json to your liking
- Add whatever you want to index.md
- Add some posts

## To make a post
- Run
        python runner.py -n "mysimplesite" -p True
- Fill in the title etc
- Edit the file that was created

## To generate site
- To serve locally
        python runner.py -n "mysimplesite" -s True
- Then open the link that is displayed
- To just generate
        python runner.py -n "mysimplesite" -p True

# Tips
- If you want to add math support to your websites, add the following code to the head of the layout
```
<script type="text/javascript" async
  src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/mathjax/2.7.7/MathJax.js?config=TeX-MML-AM_CHTML">
</script>
```
